Durban - One person has died after a truck and bakkie collided at the R603 and R624 intersection between Umbumbulu and Richmond Road in KwaZulu-Natal on Monday. Shawn Herbst, a spokesperson for Netcare 911, said the collision happened just after 8 am. Paramedics assessed the scene and found that the truck driver escaped without injury. However three occupants of the bakkie, all women, sustained serious injuries. "Rescue crews had to use the Jaws of Life to free them from the vehicle. The driver and back passenger required Advanced Life Support intervention to stabilise them. The front passenger sustained critical injuries. Due to the nature of the patients injuries the Netcare 5 specialised helicopter ambulance was activated to airlift the patient to hospital,"he explained. Herbst said while the patient was being treated her condition deteriorated and she sadly had succumbed to her injuries. Police and emergency services were on scene. The cause of the collision is unknown at this stage. Daily News 